You can find new version of the timemachine at:
http://www.net.t-labs.tu-berlin.de/research/tm/

Please think about subscribing to tm-announce@lists.net.t-labs.tu-berlin.de,
where bugfixes ans new relaeses will be announced (very low volume). In order
to subscribe, visit: 
http://lists.net.t-labs.tu-berlin.de/cgi-bin/mailman/listinfo/tm-announce
 

 see Documentation/TM_HOWTO

see also Documentation/TUNING on how to get good
performance from the timemachine

And don't forget the papers about the TM and about coupling a TM 
with a NIDS.

ATTENTION FreeBSD Users: You really want to read the MEMORY
ALLOCATOR section of the the TUNING file.
